$ Advanced Linux Sound Architecture
@ ALSA


ALSA deprecated ‚Üí Linux/sound/OSS with Linux 2.6 since when ALSA is Linux' default sound system.

ALSA is used in frameworks such as ‚Üí Linux/sound/JACK or ‚Üí Linux/sound/PulseAudio.

Apparently, a user must belong to the ‚Üí Linux/group#group-audio group to access ALSA devices.

{ Configuring

 `‚Üí Linux/fhs/usr/share/alsa/alsa_conf` is the main entry point for configuring the ALSA system.

